   U.S. ATLAS Software Support          Maintenance - Stats
                  US ATLAS Software Server
                                             BNL PAS group
   ATLAS Computing - US ATLAS Computing

   Services

     * ATLAS software repository
       cvsweb and LXR are updated every 3 hours.
          + LXR
               o Hyperlinked code browsing: top level, ATLAS, external
               o Code searches: identifier search, free text search, file
                 search
          + CVS Recent commit history - Commits by user - cvsweb
     * Local U.S. ATLAS repository
       (CVSROOT=/afs/rhic/usatlas/project/cvslocal)
       cvsweb reflects updates in real time, and LXR is updated hourly.
          + cvsweb browser
          + LXR browser
          + Commit log
     * Databases
          + MySQL at BNL , including information on the access to MySQL
            databases and installation of MySQL software.
          + MySQL browser (user/pass is the same as the ATLAS web site)
            Warning: there are several incorrect links to documentation at
            the MySQL browser web page that are generated by the external
            package phpMyAdmin. This documentation can be found at the
            MySQL home page.
          + MySQL browser for MySQL server running on db1.usatlas.bnl.gov
            (under development, the same user/pass).
     * Magda distributed data manager
       Handles cataloging and replication of ATLAS data in CERN stage, BNL
       Tier 1 areas on disk and in HPSS (tilecal testbeam data), and ATLAS
       code.
     * Project planning
       WBS, schedule, personnel. Based on the XProject tool.
          + Main planning page
               o US ATLAS planning
               o US ATLAS grid computing planning
               o ATLAS planning
     * US ATLAS Tier 1 Facility usage monitor
       Shows farm machines, their status, usage, available disk space etc.
     * HyperNews
       Web and email based discussion forums (and mirrors of some mailing
       lists)
     * Java servlets
          + Tomcat status
          + A way to integrate your servlet with Tomcat 3.2.3 and Apache
            web server.
     * Search:
          + UdmSearch

   Documentation

     * ATLAS/HENP software
          + Gaudi6
          + Gaudi5
          + ROOT: doc - Current class doc - CINT
     * Databases
          + MySQL: manual - mm README, apidoc, mm.doc
          + MySQL C++ API
     * Web server
          + Apache manual
          + PHP
          + Servlets: Java Servlet 2.2 (javax.servlet), Spec (pdf)
          + Jakarta: Tomcat doc
     * Java
          + JDK 1.2.2: Standard edition doc - API - JDBC
          + JAS: Release notes
          + Colt
     * XML
          + XML specification
          + XML4J doc, API doc
          + DOM2 doc
     * Unix tools
          + CVS (pdf)
          + Perl
          + emacs

